{d="The Old Forest lies on the border between the Shire and Bree-land. For years beyond memory it has been a forbidding place, which Men and hobbits alike have shunned. Hobbit-tales tell that the trees are aware and can move of their own accord.",id=1018,level=6,name="The Old Forest",o="Find Bald Hill\nFind The Weaver's Den\nFind Tom Bombadil's House\nFind Goldberry's Spring\nFind Bonfire Glade",pois={{locations={"31.51S, 59.05W","31.72S, 59.14W","31.80S, 58.89W","31.80S, 59.18W"},name="Bald Hill",zone="Bree-land"},{locations={"31.5S, 59.0W"},name="Bald Hill",zone="Old Forest"},{locations={"32.76S, 60.70W"},name="Bonfire Glade",zone="Bree-land"},{locations={"32.8S, 60.7W"},name="Bonfire Glade",zone="Old Forest"},{locations={"31.01S, 59.21W","31.05S, 59.41W"},name="Goldberry's Spring",zone="Bree-land"},{locations={"31.1S, 59.4W"},name="Goldberry's Spring",zone="Old Forest"},{locations={"36.8S, 57.6W"},name="The Weaver's Den",zone="Old Forest"},{locations={"36.79S, 57.56W","36.87S, 56.81W"},name="The Weaver's Den",zone="Bree-land"},{locations={"32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil's House",zone="Bree-land"},{locations={"32.6S, 57.3W"},name="Tom Bombadil's House",zone="Old Forest"}},t="Explorer",virtues={{val="Wisdom"}},zone="Bree-land"},
